Salixtools is a collection of command line (ncurses) system tools for
Salix. They can be also used in any other Slackware derivative.

It includes:
- clocksetup: configures system date and time
- keyboardsetup: selects the system wide keymap
- localesetup: selects the system locale
- netsetup: do basic network configuration
- reposetup: selects the repository mirror to use for package management
- service: manages system services from the command line
- servicesetup: manages system services interactively
- update-all: updates all sorts of caches (pango, mime etc)
- usersetup: manages user accounts

